                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33335",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rytmis",
                        "name": "rytmis",
                        "displayName": "Lauri Kotilainen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Repro in Zend 1.8.1:\n{noformat}\n<?php\n    require_once('Zend\/Date.php');\n    date_default_timezone_set('Europe\/Helsinki');\n    $date = Zend_Date::now()->getDate();\n    echo $date->toString() . PHP_EOL;\n{noformat}\nresult:\n{noformat}8.8.2009 23.00.00{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rytmis",
                        "name": "rytmis",
                        "displayName": "Lauri Kotilainen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-09T06:38:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-09T06:38:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48368",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hschletz",
                        "name": "hschletz",
                        "displayName": "Holger Schletz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The bug still persists as of 1.11.10. Precisely, the result of getDate() is 1 hour off when DST is in effect for the given date. For dates without DST or when the timezone is set to UTC\/GMT, the result is correct. Example:\r\n\r\n{noformat}date_default_timezone_set('Europe\/Berlin');\r\n\r\n\/\/ DST in effect: result incorrect\r\n$date = new Zend_Date('2010-06-20 14:56:33');\r\n$date = $date->getDate();\r\necho $date->toString() . PHP_EOL;\r\n\r\n\/\/ no DST in effect: result correct\r\n$date = new Zend_Date('2010-12-20 14:56:33');\r\n$date = $date->getDate();\r\necho $date->toString() . PHP_EOL;\r\n{noformat}\r\nResult:\r\n{noformat}19.06.2010 23:00:00\r\n20.12.2010 00:00:00\r\n{noformat}\r\nThe substitute solution with setting the time to midnight works either way. getDate() itself is currently unusable for DST-aware timezones.\r\n\r\nThe unit test only checks for 2002-01-04 (no DST) and therefore succeeds. A second check with a DST date is required for a full test. Additionally, the checks should be performed with timezone set to both UTC and a DST-aware timezone. The current test appears to use Indian\/Maldives, which did NOT show the erratic behavior with my own test script. No DST on the maldives, I suppose. I'd recommend a timezone that is more than 1 hour away from UTC, so that it's clear whether the offset comes from the timezone or from DST.\r\n\r\nThe inconsistency of this bug's history may result from the use of Zend_Date::now() for testing. The reports come from mid-October and August (DST in effect), while the fix was made in November (no DST, no erratic behavior).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hschletz",
                        "name": "hschletz",
                        "displayName": "Holger Schletz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-07T16:01:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-07T16:01:28.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
